; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
; Starter `wodoc build` configuration for a single-package project.
;
; Copy this file to doc/wodoc in your project and build with:
;
;   wodoc build --config doc/wodoc --out _site/dev --label dev
;
; That already gives a styled, self-contained site: wodoc ships a default theme
; and top bar, linked by per-version relative paths (works at any deploy path).
; To customise the look, see the menu.html and css/ examples next to this file
; and the README. Full walkthrough: the "Building a complete site" manual page.
; ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

(project myproj)            ; the opam/dune package name; also the URL path segment
(title "My Project")        ; shown in <title> and the top bar
(url-prefix /myproj)        ; the URL path the site is served at (for the version selector)
(packages myproj)           ; the odoc package(s) to assemble; omit to assemble every
                            ; subtree `dune build @doc` produces
(landing myproj/index.html) ; the page the version root redirects to (your home page)

; The left navigation. One (section …) per manual group and one (api-section …)
; for the API. Each (link "Label" <path> <id>):
;   <path> is relative to the version root (e.g. myproj/tutorial.html),
;   <id>   is the page's odoc name, used to highlight the current entry.
; Adjust the module path (Myproj) to your library's top module.
(nav
 (section "Manual"
  (link "Overview" myproj/index.html index)
  (link "Tutorial" myproj/tutorial.html tutorial))
 (api-section "API"
  (link "API overview" myproj/Myproj/index.html Myproj)))

; --- Optional: use your own theme/menu instead of the built-in defaults --------
; The menu.html and css/ files next to this config are examples. To use them,
; uncomment the line below (relative hrefs are copied per-version, so the site
; stays self-contained) and pass --menu doc/menu.html to `wodoc build`:
;   (css css/style.css css/ocsigen-odoc.css)
